/**
 * The following classes and types exist for a Speaker ID data format for
 * Platform builds 3.0.0 and above. Some of them are awkwardly named to
 * not conflict with current speaker ID naming conventions.
 *
 * Once a critical mass of people have converted to build 3.0.0 and above,
 * we should deprecate the above classes and change the names of these below
 * to be more reflective of what they are.
 *
 * Speaker ID data flow in the SSM will also change in reference to this update.
 */

